planSettings.description:
nSuns 5/3/1 is a linear progression powerlifting program that was inspired by Jim Wendler’s 5/3/1 strength program.
It progresses on a weekly basis, making it well suited for late stage novice and early intermediate lifters.
It is known for its challenging amount of volume. Those who stick with it tend to find great results from the additional work capacity.

This program was taken from: https://liftvault.com/programs/powerlifting/n-suns-lifting-spreadsheets/ Features
  • 4 Weeks of training
  • 6 training days per week

How to use:

The first week will establish your 1RM maxs for the program. You can set the program in the past by one week and go back and enter your 1RM's. The program will automatically detect your 1RM and update the values as you progress.
